commit.message:
lib/Clone/Choose.pm: document behavior of can

Add documentation which described how the 'can' function behaves.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

t/: add load fail tests for broken modules

Add a test for simulating loading existing, syntactically correct
but "incomplete" module to test even the last drop of edge case
handling in import functionality.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

t/11-load-without-mr.t: test use failure

Test whether the fallback function for use_module can handle
failures during use correctly.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

lib/Clone/Choose.pm: eliminate BEGIN block

To avoid a test coverage vs. safety situation, initialize the
module loader using a dedicated probe instead of condition check
in BEGIN block.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

t/11-load-without-mr.t: boost test coverage

Extend test coverage of branches to 92.3%. But this also reduces
the test coverage of conditions. This seems to point to a bug in
Devel::Cover.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>
Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

t/09-can-fail.t: boost test coverage

Extend test coverage of branches to 90.6%.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>
Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

t/08-import-fail.t: boost test coverage

Extend test coverage of conditions to 100%.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>
Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

Makefile.PL: fix repository URL

Fix minor typo in repository URL for non-idiot-proof parsers.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

Update Changelog and bump version for release.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/08-import-fail.t: fix test

Fix test if Module::Runtime is not installed. This should fix
RT#125045 reported by SREZIC.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Update Changelog and bump version for release.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

lib/Clone/Choose.pm: add CI test result header

Add a header for html rendered documentation page which contains short
information about development status inspired by Hash::Merge::Extra.

Thanks to @mr-mixas and @haarg for the inspiration and tooling support.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Sanbox/Tumble.pm: Added testcases

Added testcases for the situation when Module::Runtime is not
available.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/inline/09-get_backends.t: added test

Added testcase for the get_backends function.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/08-import-fail.t: added test

Added a testcase for trying to import a function that is not
supported by the backend.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

lib/Clone/Choose.pm: remove unnecessary return

Remove an unnecessary return.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

.travis.yml: play with https://coveralls.io/

Improve .travis.yml to do some coverage tests and report them to https://coveralls.io/

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

xt/perltidy.t: exclude auto generated tests

Exclude auto generated tests from tidy check.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Makefile.PL: removal of t/Auto directory

Remove the "t/Auto" testing directory to generate it new when
Makefile.PL is executed.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Update Changelog and bump version for release.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/inline/01-simple.t: load module to test later ...

First prove whether all prerequisites are available for particular backend
testing, then start testing ...

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

Update Changelog and bump version for release.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/inline/01-simple.t: don't fail test if backend not found

Do not fail the simple test if one of the backends selected vie
CLONE_CHOOSE_PREFFERED_BACKEND is not available.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Update Changelog and bump version for release.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

MANIFEST.SKIP: fix copy & paste error

Removed dist pattern and added Clone-Choose-.*

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

t/inline/01-simple.t: use simple test with different backends

Use test 01-simple.t with all supported backends.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

lib/Clone/Choose.pm: automate 00-load.t

Make use of 00-load.t for different backends. Ensure that all
functions respect the environment variable.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Sandbox/Tumble.pm: use inline test templates

Make use of inline tests. This helps not to fail if . is not in
@INC.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Hermes <hermes@cpan.org>

Changes: prepare for release

Note striking change and bump for a new release.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>

MANIFEST.SKIP: avoid distributing Sandbox

Unfortunately Sandbox creeped into unlucky distribution. Fixes issue#2
reported by Slaven Rezi.

Signed-off-by: Jens Rehsack <sno@netbsd.org>
